[JSR-305][1] is a &quot;Java Specification Request&quot; to extend the specification. `@Nullable` etc. were part of it; however it appears to be &quot;dormant&quot; (or frozen) ever since ([See this SO question][2]). So to use these annotations, you have to add the library yourself.

[FindBugs][3] was renamed to [SpotBugs][4] and is being developed under that name.

For maven this is the *current* **annotation-only** dependency (other integrations [here][5]):

    &lt;dependency&gt;
      &lt;groupId&gt;com.github.spotbugs&lt;/groupId&gt;
      &lt;artifactId&gt;spotbugs-annotations&lt;/artifactId&gt;
      &lt;version&gt;4.2.0&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

If you wish to use the full plugin, refer to the documentation of SpotBugs.

  [1]: https://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=305
  [2]: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2289694/what-is-the-status-of-jsr-305
  [3]: https://github.com/findbugsproject/findbugs
  [4]: https://github.com/spotbugs/spotbugs
  [5]: https://github.com/spotbugs/spotbugs#using-spotbugs

