The comment from @DanMasek brought me to an answer. I looked at the C++ implementation for convexHull() to see how the output param could be two different types. The C++ function accepts parameter &quot;bool returnPoints&quot; which selects to output Points vs. indexes. The Java binding does not have this parameter and I can&#39;t find the Java binding code, but Dan is surely right: since Java&#39;s convexHull output param is MatOfInt, it must be returning indexes. With some research, I discovered that the indexes are into the contour&#39;s array of Point. So, I create a MatOfPoint (same as contour) to pass to contourArea.

    private double getHullArea() {
        MatOfInt hullIndexMat = new MatOfInt();
        Imgproc.convexHull(contour, hullIndexMat);

        // convert hull indexes to points
        Point[] contourPoints = contour.toArray();
        List&lt;Integer&gt; hullIndices = hullIndexMat.toList();
        Point[] hullPoints = new Point[hullIndices.size()];
        for (int h = 0; h &lt; hullIndices.size(); ++h) {
            hullPoints[h] = contourPoints[hullIndices.get(h)];
        }
        var hullMat = new MatOfPoint(hullPoints);

        return Imgproc.contourArea(hullMat);
    }

